---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="About — Anubis Grind">
  <section class="about">
    <p>
      Anubis Grind feels like standing at a threshold you're not sure you're ready to
      cross—dark, heavy, and grounded in that brooding '90s-style rock where the guitars
      carry weight and the silence between notes matters just as much. It lives in tension:
      anger without explosion, sadness without surrender, and a constant pull between falling
      apart and pushing forward. There's a raw, almost uncomfortable honesty to it, like
      something exposed under dim light—unpolished, a little haunted, but real. The energy
      shifts between dense, crushing moments and stripped-down passages that feel intimate
      and uneasy, never fully letting you settle. It's less about telling a clear story and
      more about creating a mood—unsettled but grounded, restless but controlled—like
      drifting through something vast and undefined, knowing there's meaning there, even if
      you can't quite name it.
    </p>
    <p>
      The project blends human composition with AI-assisted production, rooted in the dark
      textures of hard rock, alternative and grunge, with atmospheric elements woven
      throughout. Created by a human multi-instrumentalist and systems architect, the project
      explores where identity fractures between human soul and synthetic sound. Songs are
      developed through a recursive process of human writing, performance, and AI
      reinterpretation, resulting in a sound that feels both familiar and unsettling.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 10rem 2rem 6rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .about p {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.9;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-align: center;
  }
</style>
